data.meta_description: LOUIS XV, KING OF FRANCE & NAVARRE ~Painting of the Royal Family of France before Louis XV (to be) was born: 1709 Duke of Brittany with his father Louis, Duke of Burgundy, his grandfather Louis, Le Grand Dauphin & his gt-grandfather King Louis XIV (seated, of course --according to etiquette--Louis created-- in 1709, no one, even in his family, could sit in a chair with arms in public in the kings presence-- officially) Louis XV, not yet born. Louis loved that spotted dog. He's all in brown.
